  "prompt": "How is EMI calculated for staff loans in SBI (especially home loans)?",
  "response": "In SBI, EMI (Equated Monthly Installment) for staff loans, including home loans, is typically calculated using the following methods:\n\n1. Calculation Formula\n- EMI = [P x R x (1+R)^N] / [(1+R)^N - 1]\n- Where:\n  P = Principal loan amount\n  R = Monthly interest rate\n  N = Total number of months/installments\n\n2. Staff Loan Benefits\n- Lower interest rates (usually 1-2% below market rates)\n- Preferential processing\n- Reduced or waived processing fees\n\n3. Typical Interest Rates for Staff\n- Home Loans: Around 6.75% - 7.50% (subject to change)\n- Personal Loans: Slightly higher rates\n\n4. Calculation Factors\n- Loan tenure\n- Loan amount\n- Credit score\n- Employee grade/seniority\n\n5. Additional Features\n- Longer repayment periods\n- Flexible prepayment options\n- Reduced documentation\n\n6. Exact Calculation\n- Best to use SBI's online EMI calculator\n- Consult SBI branch for precise, current rates\n\nNote: Specific terms may vary based on individual circumstances and current bank policies.",
